The course introduces the mechanism of the composition of the academic texts, starting from the sources used and ending with the idea, structure and formulation of the text.  In seminars students have to present several assignments, which are aimed at increasing their capability of finding academic sources, critical analysis of academic texts and good academic writing.Objectives/eesmärkid:  - to give an overview of the main ethical and practical principles of academic writing
- to give an overview of the methods and structure of academic writing
- to increase the motivation of the students to be engaged with academic writing by practical exercises and by professional examplesLearning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student who successfully passes the course: - is able to differentiate the component parts of the academic argumentation and understands the structure of the academic argumentation - is capable of finding academic sources and to formulate his or her own argumentation based on these sources - has analysed critically academic texts and has also experienced academic criticism regarding his or her own text
